results.notes:
Yellow pileus and stipe surface with cream colored gills. Abundant pale basal mycelium with some aborted pins. Cuticle is composed of interwoven cylindrical hyphae, some with intercellular yellow pigment or what appears to be light encrustation. Spores small, inamyloid. 2(?)-4 spored basidia with basal clamp and relatively long sterigmata. Gill edge is fertile, there are some cylindrical hyphae pushing past the basidia layer, my interpretation is they are just overgrown tramal hyphae and not true cystidia. Clamps present in all tissues. Yellow-orange fluorescent, flesh not much reacting to KOH or iodine solution.l
